NAME
    Snapcall - Manages the interaction between Verto connection/callbacks and Snapcall widgets

DESCRIPTION
    Snapcall object is defined as an extention of Window object.
    Attributes and methods can be accessed like this :
        Snapcall.attribute
        Snapcall.method()

ATTRIBUTES
    baseURL [string]
        the absolute path for ressources (files, images, stylesheets ...)

    states [object]
        the call states

    meta [object]
        extra informations

    verto [object]
        Verto library handlers for initialization, calls and callbacks

    caller [object]
        various informations about user (navigator, language, location ...)

    widgets [array]
        intialized jQuery Snapcallwidget objects

METHODS
    Snapcall.ready( callback )
        States when Snapcall Master Object is ready to be used

    Snapcall.initWidget( options )
        Creates, customizes, logs and stores each widgets matching $('.snapcall') in the DOM

    Snapcall.getWidget( wid )
    	Returns the matching stored widget object

